title: Lagrangian mechanics on manifolds
type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki

Let $$M$$ be a manifold given as a level set $$f^{-1}\{0\}$$ of a suitable function $$f\colon \R^n \to \R^m.$$ The modified condition for a curve to be a critical point of the action functional among all curves in the manifold from $$x(t_0)$$ to $$x(t_1)$$ is
$$\int_{t_0}^{t_1} \sum_{k=1}^n \left(
  \fracpartial{L}{x_k}-\fracderiv{}{t}\fracpartial{L}{\dot{x}_k}
\right) \delta x_k(t) \,\d t = 0
$$
for all $$\delta x(t) = (\delta x_1(t),\dots,\delta x_k(t))^\transp$$ satisfying $$\lang \grad f_i(x(t)),\delta x(t)\rang = 0$$ for all $$i.$$
In other words, this means that
$$
\fracderiv{}{t}\fracpartial{L}{\dot{x}_k} - \fracpartial{L}{x_k} =
\sum_{i=1}^m \lambda_i \fracpartial{f}{x_k},\quad k=1,\dots,n
$$
for functions $$\lambda_i$$ called //Lagrange multipliers.//

