''Theorem.''
Let the coordinates $$q_1,\dots,q_{n-m}$$ parametrize the manifold $$M = \{f_1=0,\dots,f_m=0\}$$ of dimension $$d=n-m.$$ Let $$\tilde{L}(q_1,\dots,q_{n-m},\dot{q}_1,\dots,\dot{q}_{n-m})$$ be the expression of the Lagrange function $$L(x_1,\dots,x_n,\dot{x}_1,\dots,\dot{x}_n)$$ restricted to the tangent bundle $$\T M$$ in the parametrizing coordinates. Then the Lagrangian mechanics on $$M$$ is described by the standard Euler-Lagrange equations for $$\tilde{L}$$:
$$
\fracderiv{}{t}\left( \fracpartial{\tilde{L}}{\dot{q}_k} \right)
  - \fracpartial{\tilde{L}}{q_k} = 0,
\quad k=1,\dots,n-m.
$$
